        "title" : "How to improve at Smash?",
        "date_published" : "2021-05-30T09:21:02Z",
        "date_modified" : "2021-05-30T09:21:02Z",
        "id" : "https://rigle.dev/en/posts/como-mejorar-en-smash/",
        "url" : "https://rigle.dev/en/posts/como-mejorar-en-smash/",
        "summary": "Due to the competitive nature of these games, the topic of improvement is always on everyone\u0026rsquo;s lips. As soon as we lose in a tournament set match, our mind tells us that we need to improve something, since the other person did it better than us or we failed too many things. Playing a competitive game requires constant improvement to maintain the level.\nLately there have been some very good videos on the subject on Smash Bros Spain, but I decided to make a small introduction about what our path to improvement should be. I hope you like it!\n",
        "content_html" : "\u003cp\u003eDue to the competitive nature of these games, the topic of improvement is always on everyone\u0026rsquo;s lips. As soon as we lose in a tournament set match, our mind tells us that we need to improve something, since the other person did it better than us or we failed too many things. Playing a competitive game requires constant improvement to maintain the level.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLately there have been some very good videos on the subject on \u003ca href=\"https://smashbrosspain.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eSmash Bros Spain\u003c/a\u003e, but I decided to make a small introduction about what our path to improvement should be. I hope you like it!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv style=\"position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;\"\u003e\n      \u003ciframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share; fullscreen\" loading=\"eager\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/_FlINe0GyPw?autoplay=0\u0026amp;controls=1\u0026amp;end=0\u0026amp;loop=0\u0026amp;mute=0\u0026amp;start=0\" style=\"position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;\" title=\"YouTube video\"\u003e\u003c/iframe\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n",
        "language": "en"
    },
    {
        "title" : "My Podcasting and Streaming Setup",
        "date_published" : "2021-02-05T00:00:00Z",
        "date_modified" : "2021-02-05T00:00:00Z",
        "id" : "https://rigle.dev/en/posts/mi-setup-de-podcasting-y-streaming/",
        "url" : "https://rigle.dev/en/posts/mi-setup-de-podcasting-y-streaming/",
        "summary": "It\u0026rsquo;s been 5 months since I started recording the El Último Frame podcast with almost weekly frequency, and after this time I think I\u0026rsquo;ve achieved a pretty decent recording setup. There are elements that could be improved, such as the microphone, since although it has acceptable quality, there are much better ones that capture less noise. However, for my current situation it is more than enough to provide good quality.\n",
        "content_html" : "\u003cp\u003eIt\u0026rsquo;s been 5 months since I started recording the \u003ca href=\"https://youtube.com/c/ElUltimoFrame\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eEl Último Frame\u003c/a\u003e podcast with almost weekly frequency, and after this time I think I\u0026rsquo;ve achieved a pretty decent recording setup. There are elements that could be improved, such as the microphone, since although it has acceptable quality, there are much better ones that capture less noise. However, for my current situation it is more than enough to provide \u003cstrong\u003egood quality\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWithout further ado, let\u0026rsquo;s go to each section of the configuration.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"sound\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#sound\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003eSound\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg class=\"tw-inline\" loading=\"lazy\" src='/posts/mi-setup-de-podcasting-y-streaming/Fifine.jpg'   alt=\"Neewer Arm and Fifine K669K\" height=\"2250\" width=\"4000\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFrom the beginning I have had the \u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/3oRRCSJ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFifine K669B\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e microphone, which I bought a while ago for ~20€ on Amazon. The main problem is that it picks up a lot of noise, so having it near the keyboard and being heard at the same time was unfeasible. That\u0026rsquo;s why I bought a \u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/3oUl36H\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNeewer arm\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e to put it on the desk and be able to have the microphone with less gain near my mouth.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg class=\"tw-inline\" loading=\"lazy\" src='/posts/mi-setup-de-podcasting-y-streaming/voicemeeter.jpg'   alt=\"Voicemeeter Logo\" height=\"301\" width=\"301\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn addition, I have recently been using the \u003ca href=\"https://vb-audio.com/Voicemeeter/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eVoice Meeter\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e software, which allows me to eliminate certain reverberation that exists in my room and enhance the bass so it sounds more like a voice-over.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"video\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#video\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003eVideo\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg class=\"tw-inline\" loading=\"lazy\" src='/posts/mi-setup-de-podcasting-y-streaming/C%C3%A1maras.jpg'   alt=\"Logitech Streamcam and Microsoft Livecam HD3000\" height=\"2250\" width=\"4000\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAt the beginning I recorded with an old camera that my girlfriend gave me, a \u003cstrong\u003eMicrosoft Livecam HD3000\u003c/strong\u003e, which is good enough for its age (to put you in context, the program to configure it was last updated for Windows 7 and offers integration with \u003cem\u003eMSN Messenger\u003c/em\u003e). During this time I fixed the lighting with a very typical TikToker ring light.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg class=\"tw-inline\" loading=\"lazy\" src='/posts/mi-setup-de-podcasting-y-streaming/Focos.jpg'   alt=\"Lighting with Neewer spotlights\" height=\"2250\" width=\"4000\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis winter I made a big update in this section, buying a \u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/3pX3CUf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLogitech Streamcam\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e that offers me up to 1080p at 60fps for about 100€, and some \u003cstrong\u003eNeewer spotlights\u003c/strong\u003e for 40€ on Aliexpress. The update has been worth it, since the quality jump is noticeable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn some intermediate attempt to increase quality I bought a \u003ca href=\"https://es.aliexpress.com/item/4001018830585.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePapalook AF925\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, but I didn\u0026rsquo;t really like the colors it produced. Although they compare it with a \u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/2MWGTZS\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLogitech C920 HD\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, for me it is quite worse (Although it is true that for 30€ on Aliexpress, with current webcam prices, it\u0026rsquo;s not such a bad purchase if you have good lighting).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"recording\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#recording\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003eRecording\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg class=\"tw-inline\" loading=\"lazy\" src='/posts/mi-setup-de-podcasting-y-streaming/obs.png'   alt=\"OBS Studio Logo\" height=\"256\" width=\"256\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe main programs I use to record are \u003ca href=\"https://discord.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDiscord\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, since I conduct interviews and it provides me with sufficient quality for both audio and video, and \u003ca href=\"https://obsproject.com/es\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOBS Studio\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e to capture the screen area where the conversation happens.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn addition, OBS has the option to capture different audio outputs and inputs on \u003cstrong\u003edifferent tracks of the MKV\u003c/strong\u003e, which allows me to capture my microphone and the interviewee\u0026rsquo;s on different tracks and be able to edit it independently.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI \u003cstrong\u003edid tests with Zoom\u003c/strong\u003e to see if I could record the episodes with it, but the quality was automatically modified even though HD was set, and the auto recording has \u003cstrong\u003eterrible quality\u003c/strong\u003e (see the quality of the \u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_3dCsFz9YKU\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003efirst episode of my podcast with Trifasia\u003c/a\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"production\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#production\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003eProduction\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg class=\"tw-inline\" loading=\"lazy\" src='/posts/mi-setup-de-podcasting-y-streaming/Premiere.png'   alt=\"Adobe Premiere Pro Logo\" height=\"256\" width=\"256\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen it comes to editing, the first thing I do is \u003cstrong\u003econvert the MKV to MP4 with Handbrake\u003c/strong\u003e so I can edit it directly in Premiere Pro. Since version 2019.3 \u003cstrong\u003eit does not include MKV support\u003c/strong\u003e, so it\u0026rsquo;s a step that had to be added recently by updating the software. I\u0026rsquo;ve tried other alternatives like \u003ca href=\"https://www.blackmagicdesign.com/es/products/davinciresolve/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDavinci Resolve\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and, although I\u0026rsquo;m considering switching to it to avoid paying for the Adobe license, it also doesn\u0026rsquo;t support MKV and I have to find time to adapt.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAfter this, I import the recording to a template I have designed in Premiere. In it we can see some videos that repeat, like the intro, the outro, some sound, the episode number\u0026hellip; And I have a sequence designed with everything edited so that it\u0026rsquo;s just adding the recording, making the necessary cuts and it takes me as little time as possible.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNormally \u003cstrong\u003eI edit the audio directly in Adobe Premiere\u003c/strong\u003e. Having the information in tracks, I can work by adding effects on them instead of on each section of the podcast, saving me a lot of time. In addition, \u003cstrong\u003eI don\u0026rsquo;t add music to podcasts\u003c/strong\u003e, since when they are prepared, silences can be minimized (just as I would add it to a live talkshow), so further editing is not necessary either.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAfter this, I export with the \u003cem\u003eYouTube HD 1080p\u003c/em\u003e option.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor the YouTube thumbnail I have also created a template, in which I edit the episode number and title, change the interviewee and put a background related to the interview. For this I use Photoshop since I have the Adobe license, but it\u0026rsquo;s possible that I\u0026rsquo;ll end up pivoting towards \u003ca href=\"https://www.gimp.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGIMP\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, especially with the \u003ca href=\"https://hipertextual.com/2020/06/photogimp-convertir-gimp-photoshop\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003epossibility of giving it a Photoshop skin\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"distribution\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#distribution\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003eDistribution\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg class=\"tw-inline\" loading=\"lazy\" src='/posts/mi-setup-de-podcasting-y-streaming/anchor-spotify.png'   alt=\"Anchor and Spotify\" height=\"245\" width=\"520\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI share the podcast mainly on two platforms: \u003ca href=\"https://youtube.com/c/ElUltimoFrame\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eYouTube\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://anchor.fm/elultimoframe\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAnchor\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe first one I configure in \u003cstrong\u003escheduled premiere mode\u003c/strong\u003e, with its thumbnail and metadata, and I check that everything works correctly. The second distributes it to other added platforms (\u003ca href=\"https://open.spotify.com/show/4dDPHZeRT62vYzZzpd88ys\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eSpotify\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.ivoox.com/podcast-ultimo-frame_sq_f11042245_1.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eIvoox\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/el-%C3%BAltimo-frame/id1531748199?uo=4\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003eApple Podcast\u003c/a\u003e…) in an automatic, free way, although \u003cstrong\u003ewithout access to monetization\u003c/strong\u003e. For now I don\u0026rsquo;t have an audience large enough to consider monetizing it, and if that\u0026rsquo;s the case, I\u0026rsquo;ll see which platforms can serve me for that.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConverting the produced video to audio\u003c/strong\u003e is as simple as using ffmpeg and dragging the file to this script:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"code-block highlight is-closed show-line-numbers  tw-group tw-my-2\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"\n    \n    tw-flex \n    tw-flex-row\n    tw-flex-1 \n    tw-justify-between \n    tw-w-full tw-bg-bgColor-secondary\n    \"\u003e      \n    \u003cbutton \n      class=\"\n        code-block-button\n        tw-mx-2 \n        tw-flex\n        tw-flex-row\n        tw-flex-1\"\n      aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\n          \u003cdiv class=\"group-[.is-open]:tw-rotate-90 tw-transition-[transform] tw-duration-500 tw-ease-in-out print:!tw-hidden tw-w-min tw-h-min tw-my-1 tw-mx-1\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"icon\"\n    xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 320 512\"\u003e\u003c!-- Font Awesome Free 5.15.4 by @fontawesome - https://fontawesome.com License - https://fontawesome.com/license/free (Icons: CC BY 4.0, Fonts: SIL OFL 1.1, Code: MIT License) --\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M285.476 272.971L91.132 467.314c-9.373 9.373-24.569 9.373-33.941 0l-22.667-22.667c-9.357-9.357-9.375-24.522-.04-33.901L188.505 