twitter\u003c/a\u003e that you can configure OBS Studio to automatically convert MKV to MP4, so it seems like something where I\u0026rsquo;m going to save some time.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"final\" class=\"headerLink\"\u003e\n    \u003ca href=\"#final\" class=\"header-mark\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003eFINAL\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eI hope all this information has been \u003cstrong\u003euseful for preparing your podcast\u003c/strong\u003e, choosing components or seeing what other people in the community do. In addition to using it for podcasting, I also use it to \u003ca href=\"https://twitch.tv/RigleOP\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003estream on Twitch\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and record other types of \u003ca href=\"https://youtube.com/c/Rigle\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003evideos for YouTube\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, since the camera quality is great.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you want to give me something back, I would appreciate it if you stopped by the \u003ca href=\"https://youtube.com/c/ElUltimoFrame\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003ePodcast\u0026rsquo;s YouTube channel\u003c/a\u003e and left me a comment, subscription or \u0026ldquo;like\u0026rdquo; on one of the podcasts, since all help is welcome to try to spread it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThank you very much and see you!\u003c/p\u003e\n",
